12 §2925. Individual graduation plans
13 A.(1) By the end of the eighth grade, every student, with the assistance of his
14 parent or legal guardian, and school counselor, or career coach, and for a student
15 with an exceptionality as defined in R.S. 17:1942, except a student identified as
16 gifted or talented and who has no other exceptionality, the student's Individualized
17 Education Program team, if applicable, shall begin to develop an Individual
18 Graduation Plan to guide the next academic year's course work and to assist the
19 student in exploring educational and career possibilities and in making appropriate
20 secondary and postsecondary education decisions as part of an overall postsecondary
21 plan.
22 * * *
23 (3) By the end of the tenth grade, each student's Individual Graduation Plan,
24 based on the student's academic record, talents, and interests, shall outline high
25 school graduation requirements relevant to the student's chosen postsecondary goals.
26 Each student, with the assistance of his parent or legal guardian, and school
